For the transferOwnership function, it has one argument and its type is address.

  - When the ether just received (i.e., msg.value) equals to 0:
    - the state variable pot will be updated to pot.

      - it transfers ether valued 0 to promoter1.
      - When the call or transfer succeeds:
        - For the first argument:
          - the profit of caller will be updated to (the profit of caller+the ether just received (i.e., msg.value)).
        - the lastinvest of caller will be updated to current time.
        - the usersequentialdeposits of caller will be updated to (the usersequentialdeposits of caller+1).

        - the profit of caller will be updated to (the profit of caller+the ether just received (i.e., msg.value)).
        - For users, except for the first argument:
          - When the first argument equals to 1:
            - the profit of caller will be updated to (the profit of caller+the ether just received (i.e., msg.value)).

  - When the profit of caller is smaller than 0x8aeaa9f6f9a90000:

      - When the profit of caller is smaller than 0x37a661c10d510000:
        - When the profit of caller is smaller than 0x16345785d8a0000:
          - the lastinvest of caller will be updated to current time.
          - the lastwithdraw of caller will be updated to current time.
        - When 0x3782dace9d900000 is smaller than the profit of caller, and the profit of caller is not smaller than 0x16345785d8a0000:
          - the lastinvest of caller will be updated to current time.
          - the lastwithdraw of caller will be updated to current time.

        - the lastinvest of caller will be updated to current time.
        - the lastwithdraw of caller will be updated to current time.
    - When the profit of caller is smaller than 0x37a661c10d510000, and the profit of caller is smaller than 0x16345785d8a0000, and 0x8ac7230489e80000 is smaller than the profit of caller, and the profit of caller is not smaller than 0x614885dc037d0000:
      - the lastinvest of caller will be updated to current time.
      - the lastwithdraw of caller will be updated to current time.
  - When the profit of caller is smaller than 0x16345785d8a0000, and the profit of caller is smaller than 0x37a661c10d510000, and the profit of caller is smaller than 0x614885dc037d0000, and the profit of caller is not smaller than 0x8aeaa9f6f9a90000, and 0xd02ab486cedc0000 is smaller than the profit of caller:
    - the lastinvest of caller will be updated to current time.
    - the lastwithdraw of caller will be updated to current time.

For the reinvestProfit function.
- When (((current time-the lastinvest of caller)*the profit of caller)/0xf07b2) is greater than 0, and for users, except (current time-the lastinvest of caller) equals to 0:
  - the userwithdrawals of caller will be updated to (the userwithdrawals of caller+(((current time-the lastinvest of caller)*the profit of caller)/0xf07b2)). Afterthat,

- When ((the profit of caller*s_13)-the userwithdrawals of caller) is greater than 0:
